{
  "id": "bootstrap-renewal-mobile",
  "title": "Token Renewal — Mobile (jkt-jwt)",
  "description": "After an agent token expires, the mobile agent renews without re-involving the PS. The durable enclave key (Secure Enclave on iOS, StrongBox on Android) signs a jkt-jwt that chains to a newly generated ephemeral key. The agent provider verifies the enclave signature, looks up the existing binding by key thumbprint, and issues a fresh agent token — no browser, no PS redirect.",
  "spec_section": "§ Renewal / Mobile",
  "category": "bootstrap",
  "participants": [
    {
      "id": "agent",
      "label": "Agent (Mobile)",
      "type": "agent"
    },
    {
      "id": "agent-provider",
      "label": "Agent Provider",
      "type": "agent"
    }
  ],
  "steps": [
    {
      "step": 1,
      "from": "agent",
      "to": "agent",
      "label": "Generate new ephemeral key",
      "method": "LOCAL",
      "url": "KeyPairGenerator / SecKeyCreateRandomKey",
      "request_headers": {},
      "response_status": 200,
      "response_headers": {},
      "response_body": {
        "new_ephemeral_key": {
          "kty": "OKP",
          "crv": "Ed25519",
          "x": "bmV3X2VwaGVtZXJhbF9rZXlfcHVibGljX2hlcmU",
          "kid": "agent-key-2"
        }
      },
      "tokens": [],
      "annotations": [
        "Agent generates a fresh Ed25519 signing key pair in memory.",
        "This new ephemeral key will replace the one bound in the expiring agent token.",
        "The old ephemeral key is kept alive only until the new agent token is received."
      ]
    },
    {
      "step": 2,
      "from": "agent",
      "to": "agent",
      "label": "Enclave signs jkt-jwt binding new key",
      "method": "LOCAL",
      "url": "SecKeyCreateSignature / KeyStore.sign()",
      "request_headers": {},
      "response_status": 200,
      "response_headers": {},
      "response_body": {
        "jkt_jwt": {
          "header": {
            "alg": "ES256",
            "kid": "urn:jkt:sha-256:abc123enclavethumbprint",
            "typ": "jkt+jwt"
          },
          "payload": {
            "iss": "https://agent.example",
            "iat": 1700086400,
            "exp": 1700090000,
            "cnf": {
              "jwk": {
                "kty": "OKP",
                "crv": "Ed25519",
                "x": "bmV3X2VwaGVtZXJhbF9rZXlfcHVibGljX2hlcmU",
                "kid": "agent-key-2"
              }
            }
          },
          "signature_b64": "ZW5jbGF2ZV9zaWduYXR1cmVfb3Zlcl9uZXdfZXBoZW1lcmFsX2tleQ"
        }
      },
      "tokens": [
        {
          "name": "jkt-jwt",
          "typ": "jkt+jwt",
          "raw": "eyJhbGciOiJFUzI1NiIsImtpZCI6InVybjpqa3Q6c2hhLTI1NjphYmMxMjNlbmNsYXZldGh1bWJwcmludCIsInR5cCI6ImprdCtqd3QifQ.eyJpc3MiOiJodHRwczovL2FnZW50LmV4YW1wbGUiLCJpYXQiOjE3MDAwODY0MDAsImV4cCI6MTcwMDA5MDAwMCwiY25mIjp7Imp3ayI6eyJrdHkiOiJPS1AiLCJjcnYiOiJFZDI1NTE5IiwieCI6ImJtVjNYMlZ3YUdWdGVYSmhiRjlyWlhsZmNIVmliR2xqWDJobGNtVSIsImtpZCI6ImFnZW50LWtleS0yIn19fQ.ZW5jbGF2ZV9zaWduYXR1cmVfb3Zlcl9uZXdfZXBoZW1lcmFsX2tleQ",
          "header": {
            "alg": "ES256",
            "kid": "urn:jkt:sha-256:abc123enclavethumbprint",
            "typ": "jkt+jwt"
          },
          "payload": {
            "iss": "https://agent.example",
            "iat": 1700086400,
            "exp": 1700090000,
            "cnf": {
              "jwk": {
                "kty": "OKP",
                "crv": "Ed25519",
                "x": "bmV3X2VwaGVtZXJhbF9rZXlfcHVibGljX2hlcmU",
                "kid": "agent-key-2"
              }
            }
          },
          "signature_b64": "ZW5jbGF2ZV9zaWduYXR1cmVfb3Zlcl9uZXdfZXBoZW1lcmFsX2tleQ"
        }
      ],
      "annotations": [
        "The durable enclave key (enrolled at bootstrap) signs a jkt-jwt.",
        "The jkt-jwt payload contains cnf.jwk — the new ephemeral public key.",
        "kid in the header is the enclave key thumbprint: urn:jkt:sha-256:<thumbprint>.",
        "This chaining proves: whoever holds the enclave key authorizes this new ephemeral key.",
        "No user interaction is required — the enclave signs autonomously."
      ]
    },
    {
      "step": 3,
      "from": "agent",
      "to": "agent-provider",
      "label": "POST refresh_endpoint (empty body, jkt-jwt sig)",
      "method": "POST",
      "url": "https://agent.example/refresh",
      "request_headers": {
        "Signature-Input": "sig=(\"@method\" \"@authority\" \"@path\");created=1700086400;alg=\"ed25519\";keyid=\"agent-key-2\"",
        "Signature-Key": "sig=jkt-jwt;jwt=\"eyJhbGciOiJFUzI1NiIsImtpZCI6InVybjpqa3Q6c2hhLTI1NjphYmMxMjMiLCJ0eXAiOiJqa3Qrand0In0.eyJpc3MiOiJodHRwczovL2FnZW50LmV4YW1wbGUiLCJpYXQiOjE3MDAwODY0MDAsImV4cCI6MTcwMDA5MDAwMCwiY25mIjp7Imp3ayI6eyJrdHkiOiJPS1AiLCJjcnYiOiJFZDI1NTE5IiwieCI6ImJtVjNYMlZ3YUdWdGVYSmhiRjlyWlhsZmNIVmliR2xqWDJobGNtVSIsImtpZCI6ImFnZW50LWtleS0yIn19fQ.ZW5jbGF2ZV9zaWduYXR1cmU\"",
        "Signature": "sig=:bmV3X2VwaGVtZXJhbF9rZXlfc2lnbmF0dXJlX2hlcmU:"
      },
      "request_body": {},
      "response_status": 200,
      "response_headers": {
        "Content-Type": "application/json"
      },
      "response_body": {
        "agent_token": "eyJhbGciOiJFZERTQSIsImtpZCI6ImFnZW50LXNlcnZlci1rZXktMSIsInR5cCI6ImFhLWFnZW50K2p3dCJ9..cmVuZXdhbF9hZ2VudF9zZXJ2ZXJfc2lnbmF0dXJlX2hlcmU"
      },
      "tokens": [
        {
          "name": "Agent Token (renewed)",
          "typ": "aa-agent+jwt",
          "raw": "eyJhbGciOiJFZERTQSIsImtpZCI6ImFnZW50LXNlcnZlci1rZXktMSIsInR5cCI6ImFhLWFnZW50K2p3dCJ9..cmVuZXdhbF9hZ2VudF9zZXJ2ZXJfc2lnbmF0dXJlX2hlcmU",
          "header": {
            "alg": "EdDSA",
            "kid": "agent-provider-key-1",
            "typ": "aa-agent+jwt"
          },
          "payload": {
            "iss": "https://agent.example",
            "dwk": "aauth-agent.json",
            "sub": "aauth:local@agent.example",
            "ps": "https://ps.example",
            "jti": "renewal-token-234567",
            "cnf": {
              "jwk": {
                "kty": "OKP",
                "crv": "Ed25519",
                "x": "bmV3X2VwaGVtZXJhbF9rZXlfcHVibGljX2hlcmU",
                "kid": "agent-key-2"
              }
            },
            "iat": 1700086400,
            "exp": 1700172800
          },
          "signature_b64": "cmVuZXdhbF9hZ2VudF9zZXJ2ZXJfc2lnbmF0dXJlX2hlcmU"
        }
      ],
      "signature": {
        "scheme": "jkt-jwt",
        "signature_base": "\"@method\": POST\n\"@authority\": agent.example\n\"@path\": /refresh\n\"@signature-params\": (\"@method\" \"@authority\" \"@path\");created=1700086400;alg=\"ed25519\";keyid=\"agent-key-2\"",
        "signature_input": "sig=(\"@method\" \"@authority\" \"@path\");created=1700086400;alg=\"ed25519\";keyid=\"agent-key-2\"",
        "signature_key": "sig=jkt-jwt;jwt=\"<jkt-jwt-token>\"",
        "covered_components": ["@method", "@authority", "@path"]
      },
      "annotations": [
        "The new ephemeral key signs the HTTP message (standard RFC 9421 signature).",
        "The Signature-Key header carries the jkt-jwt, linking the new ephemeral key back to the enclave.",
        "Request body is EMPTY — the jkt-jwt signature is sufficient proof; no attestation ceremony needed.",
        "Agent provider verifies: (1) HTTP sig with new ephemeral key, (2) jkt-jwt signed by enclave key, (3) cnf.jwk in jkt-jwt matches the signing key.",
        "Agent provider derives enclave thumbprint from jkt-jwt header kid (urn:jkt:sha-256:...) and looks up the existing binding.",
        "On success, agent provider issues a fresh aa-agent+jwt bound to the NEW ephemeral key.",
        "The (ps_url, user_sub) → aauth:local@domain binding is unchanged — only the ephemeral key rotates."
      ]
    }
  ]
}
